'were clearly appalled
by the scenes.

897
00:42:21,722 --> 00:42:24,156
'There's so far
nothing to suggest...'

898
00:42:24,242 --> 00:42:25,152
So stupid.

899
00:42:25,242 --> 00:42:26,721
'..that what happened

900
00:42:26,802 --> 00:42:29,714
'was the result
of violence amongst fans.'

901
00:42:29,802 --> 00:42:32,475
They must've realised
something like this

902
00:42:32,562 --> 00:42:33,995
was gonna happen one day.

903
00:42:34,082 --> 00:42:35,993
One afternoon on the North Bank

904
00:42:36,082 --> 00:42:37,481
and you're an expert.

905
00:42:39,762 --> 00:42:41,161
Well, that's it, then.

906
00:42:41,242 --> 00:42:42,152
That's what?

907
00:42:42,242 --> 00:42:44,676
You can't go back now, can you?

908
00:42:44,762 --> 00:42:46,161
'Course we will.

909
00:42:47,762 --> 00:42:49,161
How can you?

910
00:42:49,242 --> 00:42:50,436
Because...

911
00:42:50,522 --> 00:42:52,240
because everyone else will.

912
00:42:52,322 --> 00:42:54,233
Because the game will go on.

913
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:56,233
They'll even replay this one.

914
00:42:56,322 --> 00:42:57,755
This doesn't change anything.

915
00:43:03,162 --> 00:43:05,073
l just don't get you.

916
00:43:08,162 --> 00:43:09,880
No, l know you don't.

917
00:43:11,402 --> 00:43:14,314
lt's not just me you don't get.
lt's any of us.

918
00:43:14,402 --> 00:43:15,835
l hope the rest of them

919
00:43:15,922 --> 00:43:18,641
aren't as selfish
and manipulative as you.

920
00:43:18,722 --> 00:43:21,634
What's selfish about
watching a football team?

921
00:43:21,722 --> 00:43:23,440
lt's all selfish, all of it!

922
00:43:23,522 --> 00:43:24,955
All those stupid stories

923
00:43:25,042 --> 00:43:26,475
about how your mum's cats

924
00:43:26,562 --> 00:43:28,473
are called after great players

925
00:43:28,562 --> 00:43:30,473
and how she drove
through the snow

926
00:43:30,562 --> 00:43:31,995
to get you a Cup ticket.

927
00:43:32,082 --> 00:43:33,800
You stopped seeing your father

928
00:43:33,882 --> 00:43:35,315
when you didn't need him

929
00:43:35,402 --> 00:43:37,313
to take you
to the games any more.

930
00:43:37,402 --> 00:43:38,835
And we're supposed to understand

931
00:43:38,922 --> 00:43:40,355
because football's football.

932
00:43:40,442 --> 00:43:42,876
When we think of Paul,
we think of Arsenal.

933
00:43:42,962 --> 00:43:44,361
lt makes me sick!

934
00:43:53,162 --> 00:43:54,561
l hated this afternoon.

935
00:43:55,642 --> 00:43:57,041
D'you wanna know why?

936
00:43:59,642 --> 00:44:02,554
Because if you didn't
give a toss about Arsenal,

937
00:44:02,642 --> 00:44:04,075
what are you left with?

938
00:44:04,162 --> 00:44:07,074
You pay £5 to stand
on a lump of concrete.

939
00:44:07,162 --> 00:44:10,120
You can't see anything,
you're not even safe.

940
00:44:10,202 --> 00:44:11,601
And you can't complain

941
00:44:11,682 --> 00:44:14,594
because that would be
letting the lads down.

942
00:44:14,682 --> 00:44:17,116
That'd show
you didn't care enough.

943
00:44:18,362 --> 00:44:21,115
Well, at least
we care about something.

944
00:44:21,202 --> 00:44:24,114
At least we're not in
night after night

945
00:44:24,202 --> 00:44:26,113
worrying about our lesson plans.

946
00:44:26,202 --> 00:44:29,717
Whether a Scale 3
might come up in Bournemouth.

947
00:44:31,042 --> 00:44:32,760
Perhaps one day you'll learn

948
00:44:32,842 --> 00:44:35,754
to care about something
you can't tick.

949
00:44:39,162 --> 00:44:40,117
Thanks.

950
00:44:49,562 --> 00:44:50,517
l'm sorry.

951
00:44:53,162 --> 00:44:55,118
[Front door opens
then closes]

952
00:45:04,762 --> 00:45:07,674
[Paul] Football
has meant too much to me

953
00:45:07,762 --> 00:45:10,196
and come to represent
too many things.

954
00:45:10,282 --> 00:45:11,761
After a while,

955
00:45:11,842 --> 00:45:14,754
it all gets mixed up
together in your head.

956
00:45:14,842 --> 00:45:16,275
You can't remember whether

957
00:45:16,362 --> 00:45:18,273
life's shit
because Arsenal's shit

958
00:45:18,362 --> 00:45:19,795
or the other way round.

959
00:45:19,882 --> 00:45:22,316
l've been to watch
far too many games,

960
00:45:22,402 --> 00:45:24,120
spent far too much money.

961
00:45:24,202 --> 00:45:25,635
Fretted about Arsenal

962
00:45:25,722 --> 00:45:27,155
when l should have been

963
00:45:27,242 --> 00:45:28,960
fretting about something else.

964
00:45:29,042 --> 00:45:32,432
l've asked too much
of the people l love.

965
00:45:32,522 --> 00:45:34,001
OK, l accept all that.

966
00:45:34,082 --> 00:45:36,516
Perhaps it's something
you can't understand

967
00:45:36,602 --> 00:45:38,035
unless you belong.

968
00:45:38,122 --> 00:45:39,840
But what about this...?

969
00:45:39,922 --> 00:45:41,321
Three minutes to go

970
00:45:41,402 --> 00:45:44,280
and you're two-one up
in a semi-final.

971
00:45:44,362 --> 00:45:47,274
You look around and see
thousands of faces

972
00:45:47,362 --> 00:45:49,796
contorted with fear
and hope and worry.

973
00:45:49,882 --> 00:45:51,315
Everyone lost.

974
00:45:51,402 --> 00:45:54,121
Everything else
gone out of their heads.

975
00:45:54,202 --> 00:45:55,635
Then the whistle blows

976
00:45:55,722 --> 00:45:57,155
and everyone goes spare.

977
00:45:57,242 --> 00:45:59,153
And just for those few minutes,

978
00:45:59,242 --> 00:46:01,881
you're at the centre
of the whole world.

979
00:46:01,962 --> 00:46:04,396
And the fact
that you care so much,

980
00:46:04,482 --> 00:46:06,200
that the noise you've made

981
00:46:06,282 --> 00:46:08,716
has been such
a crucial part of it,

982
00:46:08,802 --> 00:46:10,520
is what makes it special.

983
00:46:10,602 --> 00:46:13,036
You've been
as important as the players

984
00:46:13,122 --> 00:46:15,033
and if you hadn't been there,

985
00:46:15,122 --> 00:46:18,034
who'd have been bothered
about football, really?

986
00:46:18,122 --> 00:46:19,521
The great thing is,

987
00:46:19,602 --> 00:46:21,513
it comes round again and again.

988
00:46:21,602 --> 00:46:23,035
There's always another season.

989
00:46:23,122 --> 00:46:25,033
lf you lose
the Cup Final in May,

990
00:46:25,122 --> 00:46:29,035
there's the third round
to look forward to in January.

991
00:46:29,122 --> 00:46:30,521
What's wrong with that?

992
00:46:30,602 --> 00:46:32,274
lt's actually pretty comforting

993
00:46:32,362 --> 00:46:33,795
if you think about it.

994
00:46:33,882 --> 00:46:35,315
But every now and then -

995
00:46:35,402 --> 00:46:37,791
not very often, but it happens -

996
00:46:37,882 --> 00:46:39,793
you catch a glimpse of a world

997
00:46:39,882 --> 00:46:41,793
that doesn't work like that.

998
00:46:41,882 --> 00:46:44,316
A world that doesn't stop in May

999
00:46:44,402 --> 00:46:46,120
and begin again in August.

1000
00:46:46,202 --> 00:46:49,114
There's some stuff
that just never comes back.

1001
00:46:49,202 --> 00:46:52,114
And some stuff
that just won't go away.

1002
00:46:52,202 --> 00:46:55,114
And some stuff
that you couldn't ignore

1003
00:46:55,202 --> 00:46:56,635
even if you wanted to.

1004
00:46:58,362 --> 00:46:59,795
[Phone rings]

1005
00:47:05,722 --> 00:47:06,677
Hello.

1006
00:47:06,762 --> 00:47:08,161
[Paul] 'lt's me.'

1007
00:47:08,242 --> 00:47:10,153
Do you know what time it is?

1008
00:47:10,242 --> 00:47:11,641
'Yeah, and l'm sorry.'

1009
00:47:13,882 --> 00:47:15,281
Listen, are you pregnant?

1010
00:48:07,162 --> 00:48:08,561
Are these for me?

1011
00:48:11,162 --> 00:48:12,072
Yeah.

1012
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:15,552
Flowers.

1013
00:48:15,642 --> 00:48:17,394
l suppose they were,

1014
00:48:17,482 --> 00:48:18,915
once upon a time.

1015
00:48:19,002 --> 00:48:19,912
Thank you.

1016
00:48:22,762 --> 00:48:24,161
Come on, Jo.

1017
00:48:29,242 --> 00:48:30,197
Oh.

1018
00:48:33,162 --> 00:48:34,515
And chocolates!

1019
00:48:40,202 --> 00:48:40,962
lt's come just at
the right time for me.

1020
00:48:40,962 --> 00:48:43,112
lt's come just at
the right time for me.

1021
00:48:43,202 --> 00:48:46,638
l was gettin' bored with
that pub and football stuff.

1022
00:48:46,722 --> 00:48:48,633
You can only spend so much time

1023
00:48:48,722 --> 00:48:49,996
playing Subbuteo.

1024
00:48:50,082 --> 00:48:52,198
Having a kid's a brilliant idea.

1025
00:48:52,282 --> 00:48:54,193
lt wasn't really an idea.

1026
00:48:54,282 --> 00:48:56,193
lt might as well have been.

1027
00:48:56,282 --> 00:48:57,476
lt's perfect.

1028
00:48:57,562 --> 00:48:59,280
lt's not just the baby.

1029
00:48:59,362 --> 00:49:01,637
lt's, you know,
it's you as well.

1030
00:49:01,722 --> 00:49:03,633
l think we're good together.

1031
00:49:03,722 --> 00:49:06,031
l thought l was
Miss Jean Brodie.

1032
00:49:06,122 --> 00:49:09,034
l was wrong.
l've been thinking about this.

1033
00:49:10,122 --> 00:49:11,555
You're George Graham.

1034
00:49:12,882 --> 00:49:14,315
The Arsenal manager.

1035
00:49:14,402 --> 00:49:16,313
And that's good, is it?

1036
00:49:16,402 --> 00:49:17,312
lt's brilliant.

1037
00:49:17,402 --> 00:49:18,835
You're careful and organised

1038
00:49:18,922 --> 00:49:20,480
and methodical and all that.

1039
00:49:20,562 --> 00:49:21,995
That's why we work.

1040
00:49:22,082 --> 00:49:23,754
l need somebody like that.

1041
00:49:23,842 --> 00:49:25,753
And you need somebody
like me....

1042
00:49:25,842 --> 00:49:27,241
Work well as a team.

1043
00:49:27,322 --> 00:49:29,040
Not even as a team, as a club.

1044
00:49:29,122 --> 00:49:31,955
Paul, you do talk
some terrible nonsense.

1045
00:49:32,042 --> 00:49:33,475
lt's not. lt's the truth.

1046
00:49:33,562 --> 00:49:34,961
lt's all working out.

1047
00:49:35,042 --> 00:49:36,839
Wife and baby, that'll do me.

1048
00:49:36,922 --> 00:49:39,231
Who said anything about a wife?

1049
00:49:39,322 --> 00:49:42,234
We'd want to do it
properly, wouldn't we?

1050
00:49:42,322 --> 00:49:43,755
Liam? lf it's a boy.

1051
00:49:43,842 --> 00:49:46,072
The greatest Arsenal player ever

1052
00:49:46,162 --> 00:49:47,595
but it's a nice name.

1053
00:49:47,682 --> 00:49:49,354
Better apply for the job.

1054
00:49:49,442 --> 00:49:50,477
What job?

1055
00:49:50,562 --> 00:49:52,951
Rosie's Head of Year
job. l said no -

1056
00:49:53,042 --> 00:49:55,158
but now, brilliant.
Perfect timing.

1057
00:49:55,242 --> 00:49:57,153
We'll need a bit more money

1058
00:49:57,242 --> 00:49:58,960
'cause we'll need a house.

1059
00:49:59,042 --> 00:50:00,953
- Paul...
- Ted'll be pleased, anyway.

1060
00:50:01,042 --> 00:50:02,475
- Liam, brilliant.
- Paul...

1061
00:50:02,562 --> 00:50:04,200
We could live near the ground.

1062
00:50:04,282 --> 00:50:07,672
lt's cheap 'cause no-one
wants a football stadium

1063
00:50:07,762 --> 00:50:09,673
on their doorstep.
l'd pay extra

1064
00:50:09,762 --> 00:50:11,673
but we won't tell
the estate agent.

1065
00:50:11,762 --> 00:50:13,161
Mortgage, wife, kid - cool.

1066
00:50:13,242 --> 00:50:15,153
Paul, none of this is real.

1067
00:50:15,242 --> 00:50:17,631
You're behaving
like a little kid.

1068
00:50:17,722 --> 00:50:20,634
l've been impregnated
by a 1 2-year-old!

1069
00:50:28,322 --> 00:50:29,437
Oh, thanks.

1070
00:50:29,522 --> 00:50:30,955
Thanks very much.

1071
00:50:31,042 --> 00:50:32,441
Sorry about that.

1072
00:50:32,522 --> 00:50:33,921
No problem, sir.

1073
00:50:35,362 --> 00:50:36,795
Sorry, you were saying?

1074
00:50:36,882 --> 00:50:39,680
Paul, this is exactly
what l mean.

1075
00:50:39,762 --> 00:50:42,560
That was just a one-off.
Never happened before.

1076
00:50:42,642 --> 00:50:45,475
l promise it won't be
a regular feature of life.

1077
00:50:52,922 --> 00:50:53,832
Paul...

1078
00:50:53,922 --> 00:50:55,833
l haven't made up my mind

1079
00:50:55,922 --> 00:50:57,833
what l'm doing about this yet.

1080
00:50:59,442 --> 00:51:00,875
Do you understand?

1081
00:51:02,762 --> 00:51:03,717
Yes.

1082
00:51:05,682 --> 00:51:07,115
No, not really.

1083
00:51:07,202 --> 00:51:08,920
l can't see this working out.

1084
00:51:09,002 --> 00:51:11,436
- lt's my last chance.
- Don't be silly.

1085
00:51:11,522 --> 00:51:13,433
lt's just what it feels like.

1086
00:51:13,522 --> 00:51:16,434
Are you prepared
to be a one-parent family?

1087
00:51:16,522 --> 00:51:18,672
l think if we go
through with this,

1088
00:51:18,762 --> 00:51:20,673
one of us is gonna have to be.

1089
00:51:20,762 --> 00:51:22,195
No, it'll be brilliant.

