1157
00:53:57,522 --> 00:53:59,433
He's not best pleased with us.

1158
00:53:59,522 --> 00:54:02,116
Who else are you
gonna tell? The kids?

1159
00:54:02,202 --> 00:54:05,114
We could recreate
what we did in assembly.

1160
00:54:05,202 --> 00:54:08,114
Find the Durex that split
and bring it in.

1161
00:54:08,202 --> 00:54:09,920
l could lose my job!

1162
00:54:10,002 --> 00:54:12,436
They can't sack you
for getting pregnant.

1163
00:54:12,522 --> 00:54:15,434
l haven't been here
long enough for maternity leave.

1164
00:54:15,522 --> 00:54:16,921
The union'll help.

1165
00:54:17,002 --> 00:54:19,675
None of this is the point, Paul.

1166
00:54:19,762 --> 00:54:21,195
The point is...

1167
00:54:21,282 --> 00:54:23,193
How many times have l told you

1168
00:54:23,282 --> 00:54:25,193
about playing to the whistle?

1169
00:54:25,282 --> 00:54:26,715
Call me later, OK?

1170
00:54:28,162 --> 00:54:29,561
See, if we...

1171
00:54:31,162 --> 00:54:32,880
Fuck! Fuck! FUCK!

1172
00:54:35,162 --> 00:54:37,073
Come on, you useless shower!

1173
00:54:37,162 --> 00:54:39,596
This lot are crap -
get stuck in!

1174
00:54:49,762 --> 00:54:51,161
l'm not a psychologist...

1175
00:54:51,242 --> 00:54:54,154
but l'd suggest
that taking up smoking

1176
00:54:54,242 --> 00:54:56,710
the week you find out
you're pregnant

1177
00:54:56,802 --> 00:54:58,235
indicates a certain ambivalence

1178
00:54:58,322 --> 00:55:00,233
towards the pregnancy
on your part.

1179
00:55:01,762 --> 00:55:03,161
He's given up.

1180
00:55:04,242 --> 00:55:05,675
- Paul?!
- Mm-hm.

1181
00:55:05,762 --> 00:55:07,673
Mr First Thing in the Morning?

1182
00:55:07,762 --> 00:55:11,152
Yeah. We're both making it
clear where we stand.

1183
00:55:11,242 --> 00:55:12,960
l start drinking and smoking

1184
00:55:13,042 --> 00:55:14,760
and he's given everything up.

1185
00:55:18,842 --> 00:55:20,241
This is horrible.

1186
00:55:20,322 --> 00:55:23,758
l don't care how much
damage it's doing to me.

1187
00:55:25,242 --> 00:55:28,359
So if everything's as bad
as you make out,

1188
00:55:28,442 --> 00:55:31,878
how come you're not applying
for jobs in...Pitlochry?

1189
00:55:34,962 --> 00:55:37,396
l know Paul's gone
completely mad.

1190
00:55:37,482 --> 00:55:38,915
l know, l know, l know.

1191
00:55:39,002 --> 00:55:42,438
lt's just that it kind of
rubs off on you somehow.

1192
00:55:48,402 --> 00:55:49,835
lt makes a difference

1193
00:55:49,922 --> 00:55:52,356
- to how you think about things.
- Like?

1194
00:55:52,442 --> 00:55:53,841
Like today, right?

1195
00:55:53,922 --> 00:55:55,355
l want us to win.

1196
00:55:55,442 --> 00:55:57,876
- With you so far.
- l think we will.

1197
00:55:57,962 --> 00:55:59,395
Home to Norwich,

1198
00:55:59,482 --> 00:56:01,393
you'd usually predict
two-nil defeat.

1199
00:56:01,482 --> 00:56:03,916
Nil-nil if you was
on top of the world.

1200
00:56:04,002 --> 00:56:06,755
lf we don't, it's not
the end of the world.

1201
00:56:06,842 --> 00:56:09,117
Four games left.
twelve points to be won.

1202
00:56:09,202 --> 00:56:10,920
That's not what l mean.

1203
00:56:11,002 --> 00:56:12,913
lf we don't win the League,

1204
00:56:13,002 --> 00:56:15,914
l'll cope because
of Sarah and the baby.

1205
00:56:16,002 --> 00:56:18,357
When you've got
nothing else going on,

1206
00:56:18,442 --> 00:56:19,875
Arsenal fill all the gaps.

1207
00:56:19,962 --> 00:56:21,873
You end up getting in a state

1208
00:56:21,962 --> 00:56:23,361
about losing to Spurs

1209
00:56:23,442 --> 00:56:24,875
when really you should be

1210
00:56:24,962 --> 00:56:26,873
getting in a state
about yourself.

1211
00:56:27,962 --> 00:56:29,634
But we will win today.

1212
00:56:29,722 --> 00:56:32,156
Sun's out,
l'm gonna be a father,

1213
00:56:32,242 --> 00:56:33,675
Alan Smith's back.

1214
00:56:33,762 --> 00:56:35,161
Five-nil, no trouble.

1215
00:56:36,242 --> 00:56:37,197
Let's go.

1216
00:56:42,042 --> 00:56:44,033
[TV]
'George Graham off the bench

1217
00:56:44,122 --> 00:56:47,558
'to shake hands with a very
disappointed Dave Stringer.

1218
00:56:47,642 --> 00:56:49,553
'Norwich know their
Championship challenge

1219
00:56:49,642 --> 00:56:50,836
'has evaporated.

1220
00:56:50,922 --> 00:56:52,321
'Arsenal's is very much

1221
00:56:52,402 --> 00:56:53,835
'on course after today.

